# 🧪 Q09 — Clone → Modify → Commit → Push (FULL GUIDE)

---

# 🟢 STEP 0 — What to open

Use any one terminal (pick one and stick to it):

* **Git Bash** ⭐ (best)
* or VS Code terminal (Ctrl + `)

Also open your repo page on GitHub in a browser.

---

# 🧾 STEP 1 — Get your repo URL

On GitHub:

1. Open your repository
2. Click **Code** (green button)
3. Copy the HTTPS URL, e.g.

```text id="u1a2b3"
https://github.com/<username>/<repo-name>.git
```

---

# 📥 STEP 2 — Clone the repository

## 📍 In terminal

Go to a location (Desktop or Documents):

```bash id="g1h2i3"
cd Desktop
```

Clone:

```bash id="j4k5l6"
git clone https://github.com/<username>/<repo-name>.git
```

---

## ▶ What you should see

```text id="m7n8o9"
Cloning into '<repo-name>'...
Receiving objects: 100%
```

---

## ▶ Move into project

```bash id="p0q1r2"
cd <repo-name>
```

---

## ▶ Verify files

```bash id="s3t4u5"
ls
```

✔ You should see files like:

```text id="v6w7x8"
README.md
app.py
Dockerfile
```

---

# ✏️ STEP 3 — Modify a file

---

## 🟢 Edit using command

```bash id="y9z0a1"
echo "Updated content" >> README.md
```

---

## ▶ Check file content

```bash id="b2c3d4"
cat README.md
```

✔ You’ll see new line added

---

## ▶ See changes (IMPORTANT)

```bash id="e5f6g7"
git diff
```

✔ Shows what changed:

```text id="h8i9j0"
+ Updated content
```

---

# 📦 STEP 4 — Stage the changes

```bash id="k1l2m3"
git add README.md
```

---

## ▶ Check status

```bash id="n4o5p6"
git status
```

✔ Should show:

```text id="q7r8s9"
Changes to be committed
```

---

# 💾 STEP 5 — Commit

```bash id="t0u1v2"
git commit -m "docs: update README with new content"
```

---

## ▶ Output

```text id="w3x4y5"
1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)
```

---

# ☁️ STEP 6 — Push to GitHub

```bash id="z6a7b8"
git push origin main
```

---

## ▶ What happens

* Git uploads changes
* GitHub repo updates

---

# 🌐 STEP 7 — Verify on GitHub

Go to your repo on GitHub

👉 Open `README.md`

✔ You should see:

```text id="c9d0e1"
Updated content
```

---

# 📊 STEP 8 — Check commit history

```bash id="f2g3h4"
git log --oneline -3
```

---

## ▶ Output

```text id="i5j6k7"
abc123 docs: update README
def456 previous commit
```

---

# 🧠 Concept (VERY IMPORTANT)

| Command | Meaning               |
| ------- | --------------------- |
| clone   | copy repo from GitHub |
| add     | stage changes         |
| commit  | save changes locally  |
| push    | upload to GitHub      |

---

# ⚠️ Common Errors + Fix

---

## ❌ Permission denied

👉 Login required:

```bash id="l8m9n0"
git config --global user.name "Your Name"
git config --global user.email "your@email.com"
```

---

## ❌ Push rejected

```text id="o1p2q3"
failed to push
```

👉 Fix:

```bash id="r4s5t6"
git pull origin main --rebase
git push origin main
```

---

## ❌ Repo not found

👉 Check URL is correct

